{
  "stem": "7598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as we sat down, I took off my anorak, which was equivalent to-- a jacket equivalent to an anorak-- and hung it on a coat hanger.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother pulled it away and said, never leave your coat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, of course, I realized at that point that I was carrying diamonds.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We actually both were carrying diamonds.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had little money, but we knew that if we had diamonds, we could probably always get some money with it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And from then we were on our own.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was nearly 15.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My brother was 17.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we were perfectly able to cope with everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were old, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were old for our age and we coped very well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I remember in Portugal, though we were in touch with the Belgian embassy and consulate all the time to see when there would be a flying bird that was able to take us to England, I used to walk up and down the main street buying presents for my parents.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I bought my mother a pair of gloves.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I can't remember what I bought for my dad, but that was that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Portugal was absolutely safe.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Portugal was neutral and absolutely safe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We stayed in Portugal longer than we would have liked, about three weeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every time we were told that they thought there were two places on the seaplane, which landed in Bristol, what actually happened was that the-- the soldiers and the airmen who were caught somewhere in occupied countries would then make their escape through the Pyrenees, get to Portugal, and they would have priorities, you know, on the planes because they were going to come to England to fight for their country and for England.",
      "word_count": 74
    }
  ],
